docs.lead_paragraph: Foreweek trading in the foreign exchange market was a repetition of the sagging tendency in the franc and the gold bloc noted in previous week, contrasted with a firm undertone in sterling. The reaction in the franc was predicated on apprehension over the meeting of the French Chamber on Thursday, and the belief that the reactionary parties' vote would be against Premier Laval.

docs.snippet: MONTEVIDEO, Friday, Dec. 27 (AP). -- The Uruguayan Government, it was learned from an authoritative source early today, has decided to ask Alexander Minkin, the Soviet Minister, to leave the country. Officials have ordered precautionary measures...
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Friday, Dec. 27 (AP). -- The Uruguayan Government, it was learned from an authoritative source early today, has decided to ask Alexander Minkin, the Soviet Minister, to leave the country. Officials have ordered precautionary measures because of rumors of a possible armed revolt.
docs.abstract: Uruguay to expel USSR Min A Minkin; charges of Communist agitation directed from Uruguay
